sublevels.theory:
Variables are named containers for data. Every variable must be declared with a type:

```cpp
int age = 25;
double pi = 3.14159;
char grade = 'A';
bool isActive = true;
#include <string>
std::string name = "Alice";
```

**Common types:**
- `int` — whole numbers (e.g., 42, -7)
- `double` — high-precision decimal (e.g., 3.14)
- `float` — lower-precision decimal
- `char` — single character in single quotes
- `bool` — `true` or `false`
- `std::string` — text (needs `<string>` header)

`const` makes a variable read-only: `const double PI = 3.14159;`
